pull_request.title: Initial commit from release Libjade 2023.05-1
pull_request.body:
This is a first proposal for the configuration of the repo.

Decisions to confirm/modify:
- folder structure
- Assembly is a copy of the latest libjade release
- Api is copy of latest libjade release, removing documentation for entry points that require calls to random_bytes

Decisions still to be made:
- what kind of testing/ci we need

pull_request.title: Initial import from pq-crystals/kyber/ref @ 11d00ff1
pull_request.body:
This is a straight copy of the `ref/` subdirectory from [pq-crystals/kyber @ 11d00ff1](https://github.com/pq-crystals/kyber/commit/11d00ff1f20cfca1f72d819e5a45165c1e0a2816).

Is this what we want?

Some initial thoughts.
* We may want to move `test/` and `nistkat/ ` out of `src/`.
* Consumers of this probably have their own build systems, so maybe the Makefile needs to move as well.
